msgid "Salt rosters are plugable systems added in Salt 0.17.0 to facilitate the ``salt-ssh`` system. The roster system was created because ``salt-ssh`` needs a means to identify which systems need to be targeted for execution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/ssh/roster.rst:14
# 53fcd304681f4bde9e63227ddab8a420
msgid "The Roster System is not needed or used in standard Salt because the master does not need to be initially aware of target systems, since the Salt Minion checks itself into the master."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/ssh/roster.rst:18
# 36476b88e1cd47b3a17a313146c7d93d
msgid "Since the roster system is pluggable, it can be easily augmented to attach to any existing systems to gather information about what servers are presently available and should be attached to by ``salt-ssh``. By default the roster file is located at /etc/salt/roster."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topics/ssh/roster.rst:24
